I am back Home!! After one more ordinary semester, (academically, otherwise quite a dramatic one actually) finally i&rsquo;m back home! On my way back home&hellip;&hellip;
It was 3:30 am. After about half an hour&rsquo;s struggle to put myself to sleep, I gave up. I don&rsquo;t know if it was the chill of the night, the stink of the urinals or the shared berth that I slept on, I couldn&rsquo;t sleep. I decided to get up and have a stroll around. After some random walks, I sat down at the TTE&rsquo;s seat and waited and waited and waited&hellip;.
My last journey home, at the end of second sem was also quite similar. I spent a lot of time at the TTE&rsquo;s seat&hellip;unable to sleep&hellip; waiting, waiting and waiting.. but it was quite different&hellip;. I was in the elite company of Hari (Hari Charan a.k.a Prongs&hellip; his nick in CS)
That journey is still very fresh in my memory&hellip; I spent most of it with him; The morning was busy and lively with DumbC&rsquo;s n stuff like that. In the afternoon while the others were enjoying a good nap, we tried studying some C programming. [ he just loved programming and was excited about doing a lotta cool stuff during the summer] But the afternoon heat got the better of me and eventually i fell asleep&hellip;{I think, I induced a bit of sleep to him too ;-) }
That night is a most unforgettable one&hellip; after all our guys went to sleep, both of us decided to spend some time listening to songs and try to put ourselves to sleep. [ The songs of RDB aren&rsquo;t lullabies by any measure! and the train was running too fast: we couldn&rsquo;t hear clearly with just one earphone each, even if we were on the top berth]
So, we ended up discussing matters of common interest&hellip; we chatted on topics ranging from Movies to Religion and Culture to Dan Brown [he told me the whole story of Deception point in his trademark style!] to Games and Programming. I spoke my heart out&hellip; {and so did he; as he always did} [haven&rsquo;t had any other discussion which comes close to it] After a couple of hours, we decided to get down and move around, to enjoy the cool breeze, to look at the villages and the fields going past&hellip; We shared the seat of the TTE for about an hour [that was the only window where we could sit : all the others had ppl sleeping beside them] &hellip; looking out of the window&hellip; enjoying the breeze.. [and each other&rsquo;s company : I thoroughly enjoyed his.. hope it was the same with him too] and waiting, waiting and waiting&hellip;
We had already spent three nights waiting for him, but still didn&rsquo;t lose hope. We hoped he would some how return or would be found safe somewhere under the sun. But that was not to be. He never returned&hellip; and all that was ever found was his body : lifeless&hellip; The rough seas had him their victim&hellip; &ldquo;There&rsquo;s no more Hari Charan, ra!&ldquo;. Those were the words of nine.
Yes he is no more.Yet he is always here, immortal within our hearts&hellip; his memories we cherish with pride&hellip; proud to have known him and known by him&hellip; with awe and reverence we think of him&hellip; we just love him! But I&rsquo;ll always miss that call of his, &ldquo;Chogni!&rdquo;
